<HL>
   Wolohan Lumber's Sales Rise
</HL>
<DATE>
07/06/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   WLHN
</CO>
<LP>
   SAGINAW, Mich. -- Wolohan Lumber Co. said its June sales
rose 11% to $30.3 million from $27.3 million a year earlier.
Sales at stores open at least one year increased 3.1%.
   For the six months through June, sales increased 9.7% to
$141.4 million from $128.9 million a year earlier. Same-store
sales were up 4.3%.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Wolohan operates 51 lumber and building-materials retail
stores in Illinois, Indiana, Kentucky, Michigan, Ohio,
Missouri, and Wisconsin.
