<HL>
   Hong Kong's Tourist Arrivals
</HL>
<DATE>
07/06/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A3C
</SO>
<CO>
   FREST
</CO>
<LP>
   HONG KONG -- Tourist arrivals in Hong Kong fell 6.3% to
499,816 in May from 533,692 a year earlier, when the
ill-fated pro-democracy movement in Beijing started to hurt
local tourism, the Hong Kong Tourist Association said.
   In this year's first five months, visitor arrivals fell
2.2% to 2,359,000 from 2,412,000 a year earlier.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Visits by Taiwanese, the largest single group of local
tourists, dropped 11.1% in May, and those by Japanese
tourists, the second-largest group, slipped 0.3%. The number
of U.S. visitors, the next-largest group, plunged 20.6%.
</TEXT>
