WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C5
</SO>
<CO>
   MAAR
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   LAS VEGAS, Nev. -- MarCor Resorts Inc. extended its tender
offer for the limited partnership interests in MarCor Resorts
L.P.V. to July 16, 1990, from June 29. So far, about 55.6% of
the partnership interests have been tendered.
   The proposal includes the exchange of MarCor Resorts
L.P.V. units for preferred stock of a newly created MarCor
Resorts subsidiary, which will in turn be convertible into
MarCor Resorts common stock. After the exchange, MarCor
Resorts will own at least 90.5% of MarCor Resorts L.P.V.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The transaction requires the approval of Nevada gaming
regulators and MarCor Resorts stockholders. MarCor Resorts is
a real estate concern that operates a Las Vegas hotel-casino.
